Step 1: Define Goal & Scope

Decide purpose: text → image generation

Decide output size: 64x64 RGB images (small toy version)

Decide dataset size: 50–500 text-image pairs (toy)

Checklist:

 Model purpose = text → image

 Output resolution = 64x64

 Dataset size = small (toy)

Step 2: Dataset Collection & Preprocessing

Collect images + captions / text prompts

Resize images → uniform size (64x64)

Normalize images → pixel values 0–1

Encode text prompts → embeddings (toy: simple character / word embedding or small pretrained text encoder)

Checklist:

 Collect image + text pairs

 Resize images

 Normalize images

 Encode text prompts → vector embeddings

 Save processed dataset → .pt tensors / numpy arrays

Step 3: Model Architecture Design

Core = Tiny UNet / Encoder-Decoder

Input = noisy image + text embedding

Output = denoised image

Checklist:

 Define Tiny UNet layers (Conv2D + ReLU)

 Merge text embedding with image latent (concatenate or cross-attention)

 Output layer → RGB image

Step 4: Forward Diffusion Process

Add Gaussian noise to images gradually

Toy version: 10–50 diffusion steps

Each step → image + text embedding as input → predict denoised image

Checklist:

 Function to add noise to images

 Scheduler for noise levels

 Ensure input-output shapes match

Step 5: Loss Function & Optimizer

Loss = MSE between predicted denoised image and original image

Optimizer = Adam / AdamW

Learning rate & batch size → adjustable

Checklist:

 Define MSELoss

 Set optimizer (Adam)

 Define batch size (1–8 for toy)

Step 6: Training Loop

For each epoch:

Select batch of images + text embeddings

Add noise → forward diffusion

Pass through UNet (with text conditioning)

Compute loss → backprop → optimizer step

Save model checkpoint

Checklist:

 Loop over epochs

 Forward diffusion + text conditioning

 Compute loss + backprop

 Save weights (.pth) periodically

Step 7: Save & Load Model

Save trained model weights → .pth or .safetensors

Load model for inference → same architecture + weights

Checklist:

 torch.save() weights

 torch.load() weights

 Ensure architecture matches

Step 8: Inference / Image Generation

Input = random noise + text embedding

UNet → iterative denoising → generate image

Save image to output folder

Checklist:

 Load model + weights

 Convert text prompt → embedding

 Generate random noise image

 Apply denoising iterations

 Save output image

Step 9: Optional Enhancements (Toy)

Pretrained text encoder → better text understanding

Latent diffusion → memory efficient

Attention mechanism → prompt adherence

Wrap in API → FastAPI / Flask → multiple projects access

Checklist (Optional):

 Pretrained text embeddings

 Attention cross between text + image

 API wrapper



